This paper discusses the security of TLS traffic inspection in enterprise environments, which falls under the categories of computer security (cs.CR) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the implementation of TLS proxies, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE). Additionally, the paper discusses the potential impact on enterprise systems, which falls under the categories of systems and control (cs.SY) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
